<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Is this your first international interview ?</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="question">What newspapers or magazines have been in contact with you ?</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="preparation">Actually this is the second international interview .</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1004" relname="span">At the beginning of the blog , Bloomberg Channel from New York interviewed me too .</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="4" relname="evaluation">In Brazil , I have been interviewed by the main vehicles for communication .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1006" relname="span">Only the Rede Globo did n't interview me</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1008" relname="span">because of the denouncements</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="7" relname="elaboration">that I have made against it :</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1010" relname="span">the 2.8 billions reals loan from BNDES</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="9" relname="evidence">[ Brazilian Development Bank ]</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1009" relname="same_unit">and its daily manipulation of information .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="13" relname="attribution">Did you expect</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1012" relname="span">that your blog would become so famous ?</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1013" relname="joint">I was n't expecting fame .</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1015" relname="preparation">Besides , I was expecting anything .</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1016" relname="span">I have laughed a lot</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="span">because of all the repercussion</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="17" relname="elaboration">caused by the blog ,</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1019" relname="same_unit">however the main subject ,</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1021" relname="circumstance">as I see ,</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1021" relname="span">it was the changes in the behaviours of the main personages of this crisis</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="21" relname="elaboration">which were caused by the blog .</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1022" relname="joint">In the media and in the parlamentarians .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1022" relname="joint">Do you receive a lot of emails ?</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1022" relname="joint">I 've already received many , about 300 emails per day at the peak of the crisis and popularity of the blog .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1022" relname="joint">In July , I could sleep only 3 hours by night .</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1027" relname="preparation">I answered everyone .</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1027" relname="joint">At present time , there are usually 20 emails by day .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1029" relname="span">I love that .</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="29" relname="restatement">( laughs )</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1031" relname="preparation">Journalism</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1032" relname="question">Do you know about citizen journalism in Portuguese ?</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1033" relname="preparation">No. This practice is not common in my country .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1036" relname="span">The blog Vizinho do Jefferson</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="34" relname="elaboration">( Jefferson 's neighbor )</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1035" relname="same_unit">opened a great discussion about this subject ,</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1037" relname="span">since journalistic occupation is reserved to the ones</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="37" relname="elaboration">who have a diploma of journalism .</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1040" relname="span">The first unofficial and " outlaw " vehicle [ of communication ]</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="39" relname="elaboration">which really worked with citizen journalism</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1039" relname="same_unit">was my blog .</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1033" relname="joint">It is called " independent press " here .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1044" relname="span">Is there any threat</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="43" relname="elaboration">of working as an " independent press "</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1044" relname="circumstance">since you do not have a journalist diploma ?</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1047" relname="span">Yes , the journalist union can sue me anytime .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1048" relname="span">However I am not taking any job .</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="49" relname="attribution">You said</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1049" relname="span">that your blog caused some repercussions among some people .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1051" relname="question">Can you cite some cases ?</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1053" relname="attribution">About this subject , I would like to say too</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1053" relname="joint">that the journalism elite likes my work</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1053" relname="joint">and finds it of great importance .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1054" relname="joint">Only minor journalists are criticizing me</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1054" relname="joint">and trying to disturb my work .</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1057" relname="question">Have you read the Portuguese-language Wikinews coverage about the scandal ?</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1058" relname="question">What do you think about it ?</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1058" relname="span">Unfortunately not .</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1061" relname="concession">Excuse me ,</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1061" relname="span">but I have to work on my blog 24 hours by day ,</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1062" relname="joint">getting and checking the information ;</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1062" relname="joint">some other histories are investigative .</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1060" relname="elaboration">You are invited to follow the Wikinews coverture about the crisis .</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1064" relname="background">A lot of articles have already been written .</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="66" relname="attribution">Do you think</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1064" relname="span">that the internet has changed something in the relationship between Brazilian people and the press ?</segment>
